name: deaminated glutathione amidase
classes: Acting on carbon-nitrogen bonds, other than peptide bonds;
comment: The enzyme, present in animals, fungi and bacteria, is involved in clearing cells of the toxic compound deaminated glutathione, which can be produced as an unwanted side product by several transaminases.

references.title: Nit1 is a metabolite repair enzyme that hydrolyzes deaminated glutathione.
references.journal: Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A 114:E3233-E3242 (2017) DOI:10.1073/pnas.1613736114
